KWM_TYPE
  Signals what type of resource is being manipulated. The following commands are
  equivalent:

    $(tput setaf 2)KWM_TYPE=root$(tput op) KWM_CLUSTER_NAME=kwm KWM_PUBLIC_IP=54.34.32.100 kwm script
    KWM_CLUSTER_NAME=kwm KWM_PUBLIC_IP=54.34.32.100 kwm script $(tput setaf 2)root$(tput op)

  If a type is supplied at the command line KWM ignores the environment variable
  KWM_TYPE. The following commands are equivalent:

    $(tput setaf 2)KWM_TYPE=root$(tput op) KWM_CLUSTER_NAME=kwm KWM_PUBLIC_IP=54.34.32.100 kwm script
    KWM_TYPE=cat KWM_CLUSTER_NAME=kwm KWM_PUBLIC_IP=54.34.32.100 kwm script $(tput setaf 2)root$(tput op)
    $(tput setaf 2)^ ignored$(tput op)
